title: For Sale:  Price drop! Weaver Tactical 3-10x40 MIL/MIL w/ Burris XTR Rings
postcontent:
Price drop!

$200 for scope, $50 for rings!


I have a Weaver Tactical Grand Slam 3-10x40mm with MIL (mildot) reticle and .10 Mil tactical/target turrets.  New in box.  It comes with a set of 1" Burris XTR low picatinny rings.  

This is a great scope for someone wanting to get into a MIL/MIL scope without breaking the bank.  It's one of the only you'll find with variable power from a reputable brand in this price range.  It has very bright glass.  I bought it with the intention of having a slightly smaller alternative to my 30mm target scope, but just never ended up using it. 

These are serious rings you can absolutely count on.  6-screw design and a simple but effective locking nut to attach to your base that makes them easy to attach/remove and return to zero.  I've used these on two other rifles and they've always held solid.  They are about $70 bucks new.  They are aluminum so despite their beefy design they won't add a lot of heft to your rifle.

This is a great setup for someone that wants to cross between long range target, dialing in your dope, to a hunting rifle that is still practical to carry up and down the mountains and make a close shot or one all the way across the valley.

postcontent:
I am offering a brand new in box, never shot (except factory) CZ SP-01 Tactical for $625.  This is DA/SA with ambidextrous decocker  My price includes 2 18-round magazines and all of the normal factory items, e.g. lock, brush, paperwork.  I have one other brand new, OEM (third) 18-round magazine that I will sell for an additional $45 if you like.  I paid $47 + shipping from CZ Custom and can still return the magazine it, so I won’t sell that any cheaper.

I paid $625 plus tax for the pistol, so now is your chance to get a brand new, highly sought after pistol for about $75-$100 cheaper than purchasing new from a local gun shop if you can even find one.  The ONLY reason I am selling it is because I have decided to add a revolver to my collection and go with my CZ PCR and Kadet Adapter for now.  It’s a hard choice as this is consistently rated among he top 9mm pistol in the world, but for now practicality wins out. 

I will require an affirmation that you are eligible to purchase a firearm and are a WI resident. This affirmation will include that you have not been convicted of a felony, crime of domestic violence, not under a restraining order or never been mentally committed. I will also need to inspect your full WI DL at the time of purchase to verify residency, age and identity.  If you have a WI CCP that would be even better as I would like to snap a picture for records.  I WILL NOT take any reproduction of your WI DL…I wouldn’t want mine floating out there, so I don’t expect anyone else to either.  Cash only for local sales, preferably with the new $100 bills.

I frequently travel between Eau Claire and Madison and Eau Claire and Minneapolis (I’m a military reservist) and can meet anywhere in Wisconsin between these points if it's convenient to my travel schedule. 

I will hold it a few weeks to match up travel with a $60 deposit.  If you change your mind, I’ll keep the deposit, but I’ll still send you the spare magazine so you won’t be out too much. I expect this to sell quickly, but if it doesn’t I will need to return the spare mag within a couple weeks.  My price is fairly firm, but I will consider including a box of target ammunition to sweeten the deal if necessary.

Witness p full size for sale- exact copy of cz-75b (baby eagle, armalite ar-24, etc) except has a polymer frame. This pistol is new and unfired. I decided to go with the compact model. Comes with box , papers, and one 16rd mag. Again, this is an unfired, new weapon. 

Very well built pistol for the price. Trigger is awesome in SA mode. These pistols can be carried condition 1 (cocked and locked). Hammer down in DA mode (safety on or off), or half cocked (safety on or off). Also, the chamber can be cleared with the safety on.  Fits the hand better than most polymer frame pistols, and are very accurate pistols due to the 1911-style locking lugs on the barrel and tight slide/frame fit. No rattles here.

Streamlight trl-3 available for extra.

The Winchester Model 1894 rifle (also known as the Winchester 94 or Win 94) is a lever-action repeating rifle
that became one of the most famous and popular hunting rifles. It was designed by John Browning in 1894
and originally chambered to fire two metallic black powder cartridges, the .32-40 Winchester and .38-55 Winchester.
It was the first rifle to chamber the smokeless powder round, the .30 WCF (Winchester Center Fire, in time becoming known as the .30-30).


The .38-55 Winchester cartridge (actually .3775 caliber) was introduced in 1876 by Ballard. 
It was used by Marlin Firearms from 1875 on for various single-shot target rifles and their 1893 lever action rifle. 
It was later offered by Winchester in its Model 1894. Winchester continued to use the round in various rifles until about 1940, 
and also used it in a few commemorative editions of rifles since then. In addition, Marlin offered it in some 336s and it was used
 in non-lever action rifles such as the Remington-Lee bolt-action and Colt's New Lightning pump-action rifles.
The .38-55 is renowned for its exceptional accuracy at ranges up to 330 yd  (300 m). It is often used to hunt black bear 
and deer at moderate ranges, and is also used in Cowboy Action Shooting side matches.
